ation in Comparative Perspective," <i id="mwA3Y">Journal of Southern History</i>, 81#1 (February 2015), 7–40.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-History_Channel_on_the_emancipation_Proclamation-63" id="cite_note-History_Channel_on_the_emancipation_Proclamation-63"><a href="./Abolitionism#cite_ref-History_Channel_on_the_emancipation_Proclamation_63-0" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-History_Channel_on_the_emancipation_Proclamation-63" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt261" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"last1":{"wt":"Foner"},"first1":{"wt":"Eric"},"last2":{"wt":"Garraty"},"first2":{"wt":"John A."},"title":{"wt":"Emancipation Proclamation"},"url":{"wt":"http://www.history.com/topics/american-civil-war/emancipation-proclamation"},"website":{"wt":""},"publisher":{"wt":"History Channel"},"accessdate":{"wt":"13 October 2014"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA3c">Foner, Eric; Garraty, John A. <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.history.com/topics/american-civil-war/emancipation-proclamation" id="mwA3g">"Emancipation Proclamation"</a>. History Channel<span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwA3k">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwA3o">13 October</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Emancipation+Proclamation&amp;rft.pub=History+Channel&amp;rft.aulast=Foner&amp;rft.aufirst=Eric&amp;rft.au=Garraty%2C+John+A.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.com%2Ftopics%2Famerican-civil-war%2Femancipation-proclamation&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAbolitionism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt261" id="mwA3s"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt261" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwA3w"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-64" id="cite_note-64"><a href="./Abolitionism#cite_ref-64" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-64" class="mw-reference-text">Vorenberg, <i id="mwA30">Final Freedom: The Civil War, the Abolition of Slavery, and the Thirteenth Amendment</i> (2004).</span></li><li about="#cite_note-65" id="cite_note-65"><a href="./Abolitionism#cite_ref-65" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-65" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt272" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"author-last":{"wt":"Bain"},"author-first":{"wt":"Alexander"},"author-link":{"wt":"Alexander Bain"},"title":{"wt":"James Mill: A Biography"},"year":{"wt":"1882"},"page":{"wt":"423"},"quote":{"wt":"The biographical narrative makes sufficiently apparent his self-denying life. While the demands upon his energies for his private needs were at the very utmost, he was an active fellow-worker with the philanthropic band that abolished slavery, ameliorated the horrors of our prisons, and began the general education of the people"},"url":{"wt":"https://books.google.com/books?id=Qkt0AAAAMAAJ&amp;lpg=PA423"},"publisher":{"wt":"[[Longman, Green &amp; Co.]]"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA34"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Alexander_Bain" title="Alexander Bain" id="mwA38">Bain, Alexander</a> (1882). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=Qkt0AAAAMAAJ&amp;lpg=PA423" id="mwA4A"><i id="mwA4E">James Mill: A Biography</i></a>. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Longman,_Green_&amp;_Co." title="Longman, Green &amp; Co." id="mwA4I" class="mw-redirect">Longman, Green &amp; Co.</a> p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwA4M"> </span>423. <q id="mwA4Q">The biographical narrative makes sufficiently apparent his self-denying life. While the demands upon his energies for his private needs were at the very utmost, he was an active fellow-worker with the philanthropic band that abolished slavery, ameliorated the horrors of our prisons, and began the general education of the people</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=James+Mill%3A+A+Biography&amp;rft.pages=423&amp;rft.pub=Longman%2C+Green+%26+Co.&amp;rft.date=1882&amp;rft.aulast=Bain&amp;rft.aufirst=Alexander&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DQkt0AAAAMAAJ%26lpg%3DPA423&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAbolitionism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt272" id="mwA4U"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt272" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwA4Y"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-66" id="cite_note-66"><a href="./Abolitionism#cite_ref-66" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-66" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt310" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web ","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"http://www.history.ac.uk/1807commemorated"},"title":{"wt":"1807 Commemorated"},"publisher":{"wt":"Institute for the Public Understanding of the Past and the Institute of Historical Research"},"year":{"wt":"2007"},"accessdate":{"wt":"27 November 2010"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA4c"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.history.ac.uk/1807commemorated" id="mwA4g">"1807 Commemorated"</a>. Institute for the Public Understanding of the Past and the Institute of Historical Research. 2007<span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwA4k">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwA4o">27 November</span> 2010</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=1807+Commemorated&amp;rft.pub=Institute+for+the+Public+Understanding+of+the+Past+and+the+Institute+of+Historical+Research&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.ac.uk%2F1807commemorated&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAbolitionism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt310" id="mwA4s"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt310" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwA4w"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-67" id="cite_note-67"><a href="./Abolitionism#cite_ref-67" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-67" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt311" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web ","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"title":{"wt":"Slave Trade Act 1807 UK"},"url":{"wt":"http://www.anti-slaverysociety.addr.com/huk-1807act.htm"},"publisher":{"wt":"anti-slaverysociety.addr.com"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA40"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.anti-slaverysociety.addr.com/huk-1807act.htm" id="mwA44">"Slave Trade Act 1807 UK"</a>. anti-slaverysociety.addr.com.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Slave+Trade+Act+1807+UK&amp;rft.pub=anti-slaverysociety.addr.com&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.anti-slaverysociety.addr.com%2Fhuk-1807act.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAbolitionism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt311" id="mwA48"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt311" typeo